"v.夸张；夸大 【英】 v. 夸张(overstate)；夸大( overemphasize; intensify) 【考】 aphoristic : terse / hyperbolic : exaggerated(格言的特点是简短的 /夸张法的特点是夸张 的)playful : banter / exaggerated : hyperbole(玩笑的特点是诙谐的 /夸张法的特点是夸张 的)反义词：minimize(减 少) 【记】 ex(出)+ag(一再)+ger (带)+ate→一再带出 去→夸张 【例】 Mary exaggerated the size of the fish she caught. v. 夸张(描述得大于实际情况) = overstate = overemphasize = intensify; 使扩大到不正常的程度 【类】aphoristic: terse = hyperbolic: exaggerated格言的特点是简短的 = 夸张法的特点是夸张的playful: banter = exaggerated: hyperbole取笑是诙谐的 = 夸张法是夸张的malicious: ill will = exaggerating: hyperbole恶意是恶毒的 = 夸张法是夸张的 【反】minimize(v 最小化; 减少) 【记】ex 超出 + aggregate 总计，合计，集合→超出总计→夸大；ex出 + eager 渴望，热切，出乎热切的渴望而夸张与夸大 exaggerate (v.)  1530s, ""to pile up, accumulate,"" from Latin exaggeratus, past participle of exaggerare ""heighten, amplify, magnify,"" literally ""to heap, pile, load, fill,"" from ex- ""thoroughly"" (see ex-) + aggerare ""heap up,"" from agger (genitive aggeris) ""heap,"" from aggerere ""bring together, carry toward,"" from ad- ""to, toward"" (see ad-) + gerere ""carry"" (see gest). Sense of ""overstate"" first recorded in English 1560s. Related: Exaggerated; exaggerating."
